{"priority": "major", "kind": "bug", "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/drcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/drcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{247b5408-ae91-4e3c-b2f9-a21994658d11}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "drcsim", "full_name": "osrf/drcsim", "uuid": "{247b5408-ae91-4e3c-b2f9-a21994658d11}"}, "links": {"attachments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/drcsim/issues/381/attachments_page=1.json"}, "self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/drcsim/issues/381.json"}, "watch": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/drcsim/issues/381/watch"}, "comments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/drcsim/issues/381/comments_page=1.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/drcsim/issues/381/drcsim-setupsh-should-source-ros-setupsh"}, "vote": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/drcsim/issues/381/vote"}}, "reporter": {"display_name": "Brian Gerkey", "uuid": "{3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:2e35028e-9ad8-4d6a-a3a5-275159a304a9/5fa9ec73-0fec-4860-a202-e34ae23b6a12/128"}}, "nickname": "Brian Gerkey", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:2e35028e-9ad8-4d6a-a3a5-275159a304a9"}, "title": "drcsim setup.sh should source ROS setup.sh", "component": null, "votes": 0, "watches": 0, "content": {"raw": "As of drcsim 3.1.0, the installed `share/drcsim/setup.sh` doesn't source the ROS `setup.sh`, which it used to do.  Looks like it happened [here](#!/osrf/drcsim/commits/e53a2d101c5a8ad236cf8ad98212ca24bed7a1aa#chg-drcsim_model_resources/cmake/setup.sh.in).\r\n\r\nWe should go back to sourcing the ROS `setup.sh`: it's more convenient and safer for users (to avoid a situation in which the user sourced the wrong ROS `setup.sh`).", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>As of drcsim 3.1.0, the installed <code>share/drcsim/setup.sh</code> doesn't source the ROS <code>setup.sh</code>, which it used to do.  Looks like it happened <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/osrf/drcsim/commits/e53a2d101c5a8ad236cf8ad98212ca24bed7a1aa#chg-drcsim_model_resources/cmake/setup.sh.in\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>We should go back to sourcing the ROS <code>setup.sh</code>: it's more convenient and safer for users (to avoid a situation in which the user sourced the wrong ROS <code>setup.sh</code>).</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": {"display_name": "Brian Gerkey", "uuid": "{3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:2e35028e-9ad8-4d6a-a3a5-275159a304a9/5fa9ec73-0fec-4860-a202-e34ae23b6a12/128"}}, "nickname": "Brian Gerkey", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:2e35028e-9ad8-4d6a-a3a5-275159a304a9"}, "state": "resolved", "version": null, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2013-10-18T17:43:52.344001+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2013-10-18T21:02:09.931216+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 381}